00:15:24,975 --> 00:15:27,937
We included Mafia real open structure.

273
00:15:28,818 --> 00:15:30,519
You're not forced to complete a district

274
00:15:30,599 --> 00:15:33,001
you started playing, so the game can be finished

275
00:15:33,261 --> 00:15:34,542
in numerous ways.

276
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:38,902
We included all hideout and racket assignment choices,

277
00:15:39,823 --> 00:15:42,344
their consequences on the state of the underbosses,

278
00:15:43,265 --> 00:15:45,366
and how they would be reflected in the dialogue.

279
00:15:46,607 --> 00:15:48,088
Some balancing capability,

280
00:15:48,428 --> 00:15:50,689
including the completion of side activities

281
00:15:52,030 --> 00:15:53,311
for bonus loyalty points.

282
00:15:54,892 --> 00:15:56,853
We used Twine for the prototype,

283
00:15:56,893 --> 00:16:01,616
and it was really great because it's very easy to use.

284
00:16:03,197 --> 00:16:03,397
Now,

285
00:16:04,326 --> 00:16:06,887
We needed to collaborate with the writing team.

286
00:16:06,907 --> 00:16:09,009
We were just two designers on the prototype.

287
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:12,611
So with the writing team, we defined a vision

288
00:16:12,711 --> 00:16:16,072
for the scene itself, for the sit-down scene itself,

289
00:16:16,333 --> 00:16:17,934
where and how it takes place.

290
00:16:19,294 --> 00:16:21,936
So we selected an old abandoned mansion

291
00:16:22,296 --> 00:16:24,377
in the bayou that you can see on this concept art.

292
00:16:26,804 --> 00:16:28,965
Then we needed to define how the scene

293
00:16:29,025 --> 00:16:30,467
would actually take place.

294
00:16:31,167 --> 00:16:33,249
We had a prototype with design text,

295
00:16:33,469 --> 00:16:36,031
but what is it going to actually look like

296
00:16:36,392 --> 00:16:37,112
in the final game?

297
00:16:38,433 --> 00:16:43,017
First, Lincoln walks in and is greeted by one character.

298
00:16:44,238 --> 00:16:45,379
Lincoln makes an introduction,

299
00:16:45,740 --> 00:16:47,561
announcing the district at stake

300
00:16:47,821 --> 00:16:49,423
or any other big announcement.

301
00:16:51,556 --> 00:16:54,078
Then each character makes a pitch, back to back,

302
00:16:54,698 --> 00:16:57,440
trying to convince the player to give them the district.

303
00:16:58,601 --> 00:17:02,844
So first character, second, and third.

